{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"89e7b5ae-f4fe-4511-ad3e-2d359df49846","content":"The project path doesn't exist yet, but here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a **dotnet tool**:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server using stdio transport.</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n| Property | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `PackAsTool` | Marks the project as a dotnet tool |\n| `ToolCommandName` | The CLI command users will run |\n| `OutputType=Exe` | Required — tools must be executables |\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# Push (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server  # runs via stdio\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold the project with these settings?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2e4fc19c-0a37-4e5b-9646-3733aaac690a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist yet. The user is asking what they need to configure, not asking me to create the project. Let me give them guidance on what's needed to publish a C# MCP server as a dotnet tool to NuGet.org.","outputTokens":489,"requestId":"F3C5:BE897:1D4C421:219D69D:69F54E66"},"id":"7f9d36e9-4b3c-4bae-92d3-37efbe78ade1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:07:59.314Z","parentId":"1c29b4ae-2e13-4f68-8b1c-0f716a3cb86a"}
